    {'id': 'q_chunk2_002', 'topic': 'Dimensional Analysis', 'sub_concept': 'Deriving dimensions', 'difficulty_level': 0.4, 'question_text': 'If velocity, time and force were chosen as basic quantities, find the dimensions of mass.', 'options': [], 'correct_option_index': None, 'solution_logic': 'Force = mass × acceleration = mass × (velocity/time). Thus mass = force × time / velocity.'
