    {'id': 'q_chunk2_004', 'topic': 'Dimensional Analysis', 'sub_concept': 'Dimensional consistency', 'difficulty_level': 0.4, 'question_text': 'The distance covered by a particle in time t is given by x = a + bt + ct^2 + dt^3; find the dimensions of a, b, c and d.', 'options': [], 'correct_option_index': None, 'solution_logic': 'x has dimension L. Thus [a
