    {'id': 'q_chunk2_012', 'topic': 'Conceptual', 'sub_concept': 'Measurement techniques', 'difficulty_level': 0.4, 'question_text': 'Suggest a way to measure: (a) the thickness of a sheet of paper, (b) the distance between the sun and the moon.', 'options': [], 'correct_option_index': None, 'solution_logic': '(a) Use a micrometer or interferometry. (b) Use parallax or triangulation with known baseline.'
