    {'id': 'q_chunk2_013', 'topic': 'Conceptual', 'sub_concept': 'Fundamental quantities', 'difficulty_level': 0.4, 'question_text': 'Which of the following sets cannot enter into the list of fundamental quantities in any system of units? (a) length, mass and velocity, (b) length, time and velocity, (c) mass, time and velocity, (d) length, time and mass.', 'options': ['length, mass and velocity', 'length, time and velocity', 'mass, time and velocity', 'length, time and mass'
