    {'id': 'q_chunk2_014', 'topic': 'Conceptual', 'sub_concept': 'Units and numerical values', 'difficulty_level': 0.4, 'question_text': 'A physical quantity is measured and the result is expressed as nu where u is the unit used and n is the numerical value. If the result is expressed in various units then (a) n << size of u (b) n << u^2 (c) n << << << u (d) n << << 1/u.', 'options': ['n << size of u', 'n << u^2', 'n << << << u', 'n << << 1/u'
