    {'id': 'q_chunk2_026', 'topic': 'Dimensional Analysis', 'sub_concept': 'Rotational dynamics', 'difficulty_level': 0.4, 'question_text': 'Find the dimensions of (a) angular speed ω, (b) angular acceleration α, (c) torque Γ and (d) moment of inertia I. Some of the equations involving these quantities are ω = Δθ/Δt, α = Δω/Δt, Γ = F r, I = m r^2.', 'options': [], 'correct_option_index': None, 'solution_logic': 'ω: T^-1; α: T^-2; Γ: M L^2 T^-2; I: M L^2.'
