    {'id': 'q_chunk2_027', 'topic': 'Dimensional Analysis', 'sub_concept': 'Electromagnetism', 'difficulty_level': 0.5, 'question_text': 'Find the dimensions of (a) electric field E, (b) magnetic field B and (c) magnetic permeability μ0. The relevant equations are F = qE, F = qvB, B = μ0 I / (2π a).', 'options': [], 'correct_option_index': None, 'solution_logic': 'E: M L T^-3 I^-1; B: M L^-1 T^-2 I^-1; μ0: M L T^-2 I^-2.'
