    {'id': 'q_chunk2_031', 'topic': 'Dimensional Analysis', 'sub_concept': 'Basic quantities', 'difficulty_level': 0.4, 'question_text': 'Taking force, length and time to be the fundamental quantities find the dimensions of (a) density, (b) pressure, (c) momentum and (d) energy.', 'options': [], 'correct_option_index': None, 'solution_logic': 'Density: M L^-3; Pressure: M L^-1 T^-2; Momentum: M L T^-1; Energy: M L^2 T^-2.'
