    {'id': 'q_chunk2_032', 'topic': 'Unit conversion', 'sub_concept': 'Acceleration units', 'difficulty_level': 0.3, 'question_text': 'Suppose the acceleration due to gravity at a place is 10 m/s^2. Find its value in cm/(minute)^2.', 'options': [], 'correct_option_index': None, 'solution_logic': '10 m/s^2 = 10^3 cm / (60 s)^2 ≈ 0.2778 cm/min^2.'
