    {'id': 'q_chunk2_034', 'topic': 'Unit conversion', 'sub_concept': 'Pressure calculation', 'difficulty_level': 0.4, 'question_text': 'The height of mercury column in a barometer in a Calcutta laboratory was recorded to be 75 cm. Calculate this pressure in SI and CGS units using the following data: Specific gravity of mercury = 13.6, Density of water = 10^3 kg/m^3, g=9.8 m/s^2 at Calcutta. Pressure = h p g in usual symbols.', 'options': [], 'correct_option_index': None, 'solution_logic': 'p = 13.6 × 10^3 kg/m^3, h = 0.75 m, g = 9.8 m/s^2 → P ≈ 1.0×10^5 Pa. In CGS: ≈ 1.0×10^6 dyne/cm^2.'
