    {'id': 'q_chunk2_036', 'topic': 'Unit conversion', 'sub_concept': 'Time conversion', 'difficulty_level': 0.3, 'question_text': 'The normal duration of I.Sc. Physics practical period in Indian colleges is 100 minutes. Express this period in microcenturies. 1 microcentury = 10^-6 × 100 years. How many microcenturies did you sleep yesterday?', 'options': [], 'correct_option_index': None, 'solution_logic': '100 min = 0.0001905 years. 1 microcentury = 10^-4 years. So ≈ 1.905 microcenturies.'
