    {'id': 'q_chunk2_039', 'topic': 'Dimensional Analysis', 'sub_concept': 'Relativity', 'difficulty_level': 0.6, 'question_text': 'Theory of relativity reveals that mass can be converted into energy. The energy E so obtained is proportional to certain powers of mass m and the speed c of light. Guess a relation among the quantities using the method of dimensions.', 'options': [], 'correct_option_index': None, 'solution_logic': 'E ∝ m c^2.'
